Table 1 — Mandatory & Important SQL Topics (High Priority)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Category                    | Topics                                                                 | Priority Level | Why Important                                     |
|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| Foundations                 | DB basics, Tables, PK, FK, Constraints                                 | MUST           | Core understanding of data structure              |
| Query Basics                | SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, LIMIT, DISTINCT                               | MUST           | Base of all SQL queries                           |
| Filtering                   | AND, OR, NOT, IN, BETWEEN, LIKE                                        | MUST           | Used in almost every query                        |
| Aggregations                | COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX, GROUP BY, HAVING                            | MUST           | Very frequent in interviews                       |
| Joins                       | INNER JOIN, LEFT JOIN, RIGHT JOIN, SELF JOIN                           | MUST           | Most asked topic (70% interviews)                 |
| Subqueries                  | Scalar, Correlated, EXISTS, NOT EXISTS                                 | MUST           | Advanced querying logic                           |
| CTE (WITH)                  | WITH clause                                                            | IMPORTANT      | Cleaner alternative to subqueries                 |
| Functions (Conditional)     | CASE WHEN, COALESCE, IFNULL                                            | MUST           | Used for logic handling                           |
| String Functions            | LENGTH, SUBSTRING, CONCAT, TRIM, REPLACE                               | IMPORTANT      | Data cleaning & transformation                    |
| Date Functions              | CURRENT_DATE, DATE_ADD, DATE_SUB, DATEDIFF                             | IMPORTANT      | Real-world data handling                          |
| Window Functions            | ROW_NUMBER, RANK, DENSE_RANK, PARTITION BY                             | VERY IMPORTANT | High-level interview + real-world use             |
| Set Operations              | UNION, UNION ALL                                                       | IMPORTANT      | Combining result sets                             |
| Data Manipulation           | INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE                                                 | MUST           | CRUD operations                                   |
| Transactions                | COMMIT, ROLLBACK, ACID                                                 | IMPORTANT      | Backend + consistency handling                    |
| Basic Performance           | Index basics, EXPLAIN                                                  | IMPORTANT      | Improves query efficiency                         |
| Database Design             | Normalization, Relationships (1-1, 1-M, M-M)                           | IMPORTANT      | System design + schema building                   |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Table 2 — Less Priority / Optional Topics

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Category                    | Topics                                                                 | Priority Level | Why Less Priority                                 |
|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| JSON in SQL                 | JSON functions, JSON queries                                           | OPTIONAL       | Used only in specific use cases                   |
| Advanced Access Control     | Roles, Permissions, Grants                                             | OPTIONAL       | Mostly DBA responsibility                         |
| Advanced Transactions       | Isolation levels (deep dive)                                           | OPTIONAL       | Basic knowledge is enough                         |
| Storage Internals           | Disk storage, page structure, indexing internals                       | LOW            | Rarely asked in interviews                        |
| Database Scaling            | Sharding, Replication, Partitioning                                    | LOW            | Needed for senior/system design roles             |
| Advanced Set Operations     | INTERSECT, EXCEPT                                                      | LOW            | Rarely used in real-world queries                 |
| Temporary Structures        | Temp tables (deep usage)                                               | OPTIONAL       | Not frequently asked                              |
| Advanced Optimization       | Query planner internals, cost-based optimization                       | LOW            | Deep DB-level knowledge                           |
| Vendor-Specific Features    | MySQL/Postgres-specific features                                       | OPTIONAL       | Depends on company/project                        |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------